{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877276430,"sessionID":"ses_28577793bffeWlqSBWZrdZ4b1w","part":{"id":"prt_d7a88b959001OQMudI2MrYClJu","messageID":"msg_d7a88a51f001qF4VBbO0JYZRp1","sessionID":"ses_28577793bffeWlqSBWZrdZ4b1w","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_3f727ca7bf1745eaa0de59d7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028: SDK AgentRuntimeClient — Technical Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **Module:** `sdk-python`  \n6: **Language:** Python  \n7: **Size:** M  \n8: \n9: This document provides technical implementation details for the `AgentRuntimeClient` feature in the AgentCube Python SDK.\n10: \n11: ## Architecture\n12: \n13: ### Component Hierarchy\n14: \n15: ```\n16: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n17: │       AgentRuntimeClient                │\n18: │  (High-level Facade)                    │\n19: │  - agent_name                           │\n20: │  - namespace                            │\n21: │  - session_id (bootstrapped or given)   │\n22: │  - dp_client                            │\n23: └─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n24:                     │\n25:                     │ delegates to\n26:                     ▼\n27: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n28: │   AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient           │\n29: │  (HTTP Client for Router)               │\n30: │  - base_url                             │\n31: │  - session (requests.Session)           │\n32: │  - timeout / connect_timeout            │\n33: └─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n34: ```\n35: \n36: ### Design Patterns\n37: \n38: 1. **Facade Pattern**: `AgentRuntimeClient` provides simplified interface hiding data plane complexity\n39: 2. **Context Manager Protocol**: Supports `with` statement for automatic resource cleanup\n40: 3. **Environment Configuration**: Router URL resolves from argument → `ROUTER_URL` env var → error\n41: 4. **Session Bootstrap**: Auto-retrieves session ID from Router if not provided\n42: \n43: ## Data Structures\n44: \n45: ### `AgentRuntimeClient` Instance Attributes\n46: \n47: | Attribute | Type | Description | Default |\n48: |-----------|------|-------------|---------|\n49: | `agent_name` | `str` | Target agent runtime name | (required) |\n50: | `namespace` | `str` | Kubernetes namespace | `\"default\"` |\n51: | `router_url` | `str` | Router base URL | from `ROUTER_URL` env |\n52: | `verbose` | `bool` | Enable debug logging | `False` |\n53: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | Session identifier | bootstrapped or given |\n54: | `timeout` | `int` | Request timeout (seconds) | `120` |\n55: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | Connection timeout (seconds) | `5.0` |\n56: | `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Module logger | - |\n57: | `dp_client` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Data plane client | - |\n58: \n59: ### `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` Instance Attributes\n60: \n61: | Attribute | Type | Description | Default |\n62: |-----------|------|-------------|---------|\n63: | `router_url` | `str` | Router base URL | (required) |\n64: | `namespace` | `str` | Kubernetes namespace | (required) |\n65: | `agent_name` | `str` | Agent runtime name | (required) |\n66: | `base_url` | `str` | Computed invocation URL | - |\n67: | `timeout` | `int` | Request timeout (seconds) | `120` |\n68: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | Connection timeout (seconds) | `5.0` |\n69: | `session` | `requests.Session` | HTTP session with pooling | - |\n70: | `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Module logger | - |\n71: \n72: ### Class Constants\n73: \n74: ```python\n75: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n76:     SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"  # Lowercase header name\n77: ```\n78: \n79: ## API Contracts\n80: \n81: ### AgentRuntimeClient Public Interface\n82: \n83: ```python\n84: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n85:     def __init__(\n86:         self,\n87:         agent_name: str,\n88:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n89:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n90:         verbose: bool = False,\n91:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n92:         timeout: int = 120,\n93:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n94:     ) -> None\n95: \n96:     def __enter__(self) -> \"AgentRuntimeClient\": ...\n97:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n98:     def invoke(self, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any: ...\n99:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n100: ```\n101: \n102: ### AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Public Interface\n103: \n104: ```python\n105: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n106:     SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n107: \n108:     def __init__(\n109:         self,\n110:         router_url: str,\n111:         namespace: str,\n112:         agent_name: str,\n113:         timeout: int = 120,\n114:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n115:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n116:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n117:     ) -> None\n118: \n119:     def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str: ...\n120:     def invoke(\n121:         self,\n122:         session_id: str,\n123:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n124:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n125:     ) -> requests.Response: ...\n126:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n127: ```\n128: \n129: ### HTTP Contracts\n130: \n131: #### Bootstrap Session (GET)\n132: \n133: | Property | Value |\n134: |----------|-------|\n135: | **Method** | `GET` |\n136: | **URL** | `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` |\n137: | **Headers** | (session defaults only) |\n138: | **Body** | (none) |\n139: | **Success Response** | 200 with header `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` |\n140: | **Timeout** | `(connect_timeout, timeout)` |\n141: \n142: #### Invoke Agent (POST)\n143: \n144: | Property | Value |\n145: |----------|-------|\n146: | **Method** | `POST` |\n147: | **URL** | `{base_url}` (computed in init) |\n148: | **Headers** | `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`, `Content-Type: application/json` |\n149: | **Body** | JSON payload dict |\n150: | **Success Response** | 200 OK, response body parsed as JSON |\n151: | **Timeout** | `(connect_timeout, timeout)` or `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` |\n152: \n153: ### Base URL Computation\n154: \n155: ```python\n156: base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n157: self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n158: ```\n159: \n160: ## Error Handling\n161: \n162: ### Exception Matrix\n163: \n164: | Error Condition | Exception Type | Message |\n165: |-----------------|----------------|---------|\n166: | Missing `router_url` and `ROUTER_URL` env var | `ValueError` | Contains \"router_url must be provided\" |\n167: | Bootstrap response lacks session header | `ValueError` | `\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\"` |\n168: | `invoke()` called without initialized session | `ValueError` | `\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\"` |\n169: | HTTP error (4xx/5xx) | `requests.HTTPError` | Raised by `response.raise_for_status()` |\n170: | Network error | `requests.RequestException` | Propagated to caller |\n171: \n172: ### Error Handling Flow\n173: \n174: ```\n175: AgentRuntimeClient.__init__\n176:     ├─ Router URL missing → raise ValueError\n177:     └─ session_id is None\n178:         └─ bootstrap_session_id()\n179:             ├─ GET request fails → raise requests.RequestException\n180:             └─ Missing header → raise ValueError\n181: \n182: AgentRuntimeClient.invoke\n183:     ├─ session_id is None → raise ValueError\n184:     └─ dp_client.invoke()\n185:         ├─ HTTP error → raise requests.HTTPError\n186:         └─ Network error → raise requests.RequestException\n187: ```\n188: \n189: ## Testing Strategy\n190: \n191: ### Unit Tests\n192: \n193: #### Test File: `tests/unit/test_agent_runtime.py`\n194: \n195: ```python\n196: import pytest\n197: from unittest.mock import Mock, patch, MagicMock\n198: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n199: from agentcube.clients import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n200: \n201: class TestAgentRuntimeClientInit:\n202:     def test_init_with_explicit_session_id(self):\n203:         \"\"\"GIVEN session_id is provided\n204:            WHEN client initializes\n205:            THEN bootstrap is NOT called\"\"\"\n206:         with patch.object(AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient, 'bootstrap_session_id') as mock_bootstrap:\n207:             client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n208:                 agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n209:                 router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n210:                 session_id=\"test-session-123\"\n211:             )\n212:             assert client.session_id == \"test-session-123\"\n213:             mock_bootstrap.assert_not_called()\n214: \n215:     def test_init_without_session_id_triggers_bootstrap(self):\n216:         \"\"\"GIVEN session_id is None\n217:            WHEN client initializes\n218:            THEN bootstrap IS called\"\"\"\n219:         with patch.object(AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient, 'bootstrap_session_id', \n220:                           return_value=\"bootstrapped-session\"):\n221:             client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n222:                 agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n223:                 router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n224:             )\n225:             assert client.session_id == \"bootstrapped-session\"\n226: \n227:     def test_router_url_from_env(self):\n228:         \"\"\"GIVEN router_url not provided but ROUTER_URL env var set\n229:            WHEN client initializes\n230:            THEN router_url from env\"\"\"\n231:         with patch('os.getenv', return_value=\"http://from-env:8080\"):\n232:             client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n233:                 agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n234:                 router_url=None\n235:             )\n236:             assert client.router_url == \"http://from-env:8080\"\n237: \n238:     def test_missing_router_url_raises(self):\n239:         \"\"\"GIVEN neither router_url nor ROUTER_URL env var\n240:            WHEN client initializes\n241:            THEN ValueError raised\"\"\"\n242:         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"router_url must be provided\"):\n243:             with patch('os.getenv', return_value=None):\n244:                 AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"test-agent\")\n245: \n246:     def test_timeout_defaults(self):\n247:         \"\"\"GIVEN timeout/connect_timeout not specified\n248:            WHEN client initializes\n249:            THEN defaults applied\"\"\"\n250:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n251:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n252:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n253:         )\n254:         assert client.timeout == 120\n255:         assert client.connect_timeout == 5.0\n256: \n257:     def test_namespace_default(self):\n258:         \"\"\"GIVEN namespace not specified\n259:            WHEN client initializes\n260:            THEN defaults to 'default'\"\"\"\n261:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n262:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n263:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n264:         )\n265:         assert client.namespace == \"default\"\n266: \n267: \n268: class TestAgentRuntimeClientContextManager:\n269:     def test_context_manager_enter(self):\n270:         \"\"\"GIVEN with statement used\n271:            WHEN entering context\n272:            THEN returns self\"\"\"\n273:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n274:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n275:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n276:         )\n277:         with client as c:\n278:             assert c is client\n279: \n280:     def test_context_manager_exit_calls_close(self):\n281:         \"\"\"GIVEN context block exits\n282:            WHEN __exit__ called\n283:            THEN close() is called\"\"\"\n284:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n285:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n286:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n287:         )\n288:         client.close = Mock()\n289:         with client:\n290:             pass\n291:         client.close.assert_called_once()\n292: \n293:     def test_context_manager_exit_with_exception(self):\n294:         \"\"\"GIVEN context block raises exception\n295:            WHEN __exit__ called\n296:            THEN close() still called\"\"\"\n297:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n298:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n299:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n300:         )\n301:         client.close = Mock()\n302:         with pytest.raises(ValueError):\n303:             with client:\n304:                 raise ValueError(\"test error\")\n305:         client.close.assert_called_once()\n306: \n307: \n308: class TestAgentRuntimeClientInvoke:\n309:     def test_invoke_with_payload(self):\n310:         \"\"\"GIVEN session_id initialized\n311:            WHEN invoke called with payload\n312:            THEN dp_client.invoke called\"\"\"\n313:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n314:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n315:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n316:             session_id=\"test-session\"\n317:         )\n318:         client.dp_client.invoke = Mock(return_value=Mock(json=lambda: {\"result\": \"ok\"}))\n319:         result = client.invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"})\n320:         client.dp_client.invoke.assert_called_once_with(\n321:             session_id=\"test-session\",\n322:             payload={\"message\": \"hello\"},\n323:             timeout=None\n324:         )\n325:         assert result == {\"result\": \"ok\"}\n326: \n327:     def test_invoke_returns_parsed_json(self):\n328:         \"\"\"GIVEN dp_client.invoke returns response\n329:            WHEN invoke completes\n330:            THEN parsed JSON returned\"\"\"\n331:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n332:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n333:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n334:             session_id=\"test-session\"\n335:         )\n336:         mock_response = Mock()\n337:         mock_response.json.return_value = {\"status\": \"success\", \"data\": [1, 2, 3]}\n338:         client.dp_client.invoke = Mock(return_value=mock_response)\n339:         result = client.invoke({\"test\": \"payload\"})\n340:         assert result == {\"status\": \"success\", \"data\": [1, 2, 3]}\n341: \n342:     def test_invoke_without_session_raises(self):\n343:         \"\"\"GIVEN session_id is None\n344:            WHEN invoke called\n345:            THEN ValueError raised\"\"\"\n346:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n347:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n348:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n349:             session_id=None\n350:         )\n351:         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\"):\n352:             client.invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"})\n353: \n354:     def test_invoke_with_timeout_override(self):\n355:         \"\"\"GIVEN invoke called with timeout=60\n356:            WHEN request sent\n357:            THEN timeout=60 passed to dp_client\"\"\"\n358:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n359:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n360:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n361:             session_id=\"test-session\"\n362:         )\n363:         client.dp_client.invoke = Mock(return_value=Mock(json=lambda: {}))\n364:         client.invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"}, timeout=60)\n365:         client.dp_client.invoke.assert_called_once_with(\n366:             session_id=\"test-session\",\n367:             payload={\"message\": \"hello\"},\n368:             timeout=60\n369:         )\n370: \n371: \n372: class TestAgentRuntimeClientClose:\n373:     def test_close_calls_dp_client_close(self):\n374:         \"\"\"GIVEN close() called\n375:            WHEN method executes\n376:            THEN dp_client.close() called\"\"\"\n377:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n378:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n379:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n380:         )\n381:         client.dp_client.close = Mock()\n382:         client.close()\n383:         client.dp_client.close.assert_called_once()\n384: \n385: \n386: class TestAgentRuntimeDataPlaneClientInit:\n387:     def test_base_url_computation(self):\n388:         \"\"\"GIVEN router_url, namespace, agent_name provided\n389:            WHEN client initializes\n390:            THEN base_url computed correctly\"\"\"\n391:         client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n392:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n393:             namespace=\"default\",\n394:             agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n395:         )\n396:         expected = \"http://router:8080/v1/namespaces/default/agent-runtimes/test-agent/invocations/\"\n397:         assert client.base_url == expected\n398: \n399:     def test_session_header_constant(self):\n400:         \"\"\"GIVEN class constant accessed\n401:            WHEN SESSION_HEADER read\n402:            THEN equals lowercase header name\"\"\"\n403:         assert AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.SESSION_HEADER == \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n404: \n405:     def test_timeout_defaults(self):\n406:         \"\"\"GIVEN timeout/connect_timeout not specified\n407:            WHEN client initializes\n408:            THEN defaults applied\"\"\"\n409:         client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n410:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n411:             namespace=\"default\",\n412:             agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n413:         )\n414:         assert client.timeout == 120\n415:         assert client.connect_timeout == 5.0\n416: \n417: \n418: class TestAgentRuntimeDataPlaneClientBootstrap:\n419:     def test_successful_bootstrap(self):\n420:         \"\"\"GIVEN Router responds with session header\n421:            WHEN bootstrap_session_id called\n422:            THEN header value returned\"\"\"\n423:         client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n424:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n425:             namespace=\"default\",\n426:             agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n427:         )\n428:         mock_response = Mock()\n429:         mock_response.headers = {\"x-agentcube-session-id\": \"bootstrapped-session-123\"}\n430:         client.session.get = Mock(return_value=mock_response)\n431:         \n432:         result = client.bootstrap_session_id()\n433:         assert result == \"bootstrapped-session-123\"\n434: \n435:     def test_missing_header_raises(self):\n436:         \"\"\"GIVEN Response lacks session header\n437:            WHEN bootstrap_session_id called\n438:            THEN ValueError raised\"\"\"\n439:         client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n440:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n441:             namespace=\"default\",\n442:             agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n443:         )\n444:         mock_response = Mock()\n445:         mock_response.headers = {}\n446:         client.session.get = Mock(return_value=mock_response)\n447:         \n448:         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\"):\n449:             client.bootstrap_session_id()\n450: \n451:     def test_bootstrap_makes_get_request(self):\n452:         \"\"\"GIVEN bootstrap_session_id called\n453:            WHEN request sent\n454:            THEN GET to base_url with timeout tuple\"\"\"\n455:         client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n456:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n457:             namespace=\"default\",\n458:             agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n459:         )\n460:         mock_response = Mock()\n461:         mock_response.headers = {\"x-agentcube-session-id\": \"session-123\"}\n462:         client.session.get = Mock(return_value=mock_response)\n463:         \n464:         client.bootstrap_session_id()\n465:         client.session.get.assert_called_once_with(\n466:             client.base_url,\n467:             timeout=(client.connect_timeout, client.timeout)\n468:         )\n469: \n470: \n471: class TestAgentRuntimeDataPlaneClientInvoke:\n472:     def test_invoke_sends_post_request(self):\n473:         \"\"\"GIVEN invoke called with payload\n474:            WHEN request sent\n475:            THEN POST to base_url with JSON body\"\"\"\n476:         client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n477:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n478:             namespace=\"default\",\n479:             agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n480:         )\n481:         client.session_id = \"test-session\"\n482:         mock_response = Mock()\n483:         client.session.post = Mock(return_value=mock_response)\n484:         \n485:         payload = {\"message\": \"hello\", \"data\": [1, 2, 3]}\n486:         client.invoke(session_id=\"test-session\", payload=payload)\n487:         \n488:         client.session.post.assert_called_once()\n489:         call_args = client.session.post.call_args\n490:         assert call_args[0][0] == client.base_url\n491:         assert call_args[1]['json'] == payload\n492: \n493:     def test_invoke_sets_session_header(self):\n494:         \"\"\"GIVEN invoke called\n495:            WHEN headers constructed\n496:            THEN x-agentcube-session-id included\"\"\"\n497:         client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n498:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n499:             namespace=\"default\",\n500:             agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n501:         )\n502:         client.session_id = \"test-session\"\n503:         mock_response = Mock()\n504:         client.session.post = Mock(return_value=mock_response)\n505:         \n506:         client.invoke(session_id=\"test-session\", payload={\"test\": \"data\"})\n507:         \n508:         headers = client.session.post.call_args[1]['headers']\n509:         assert headers[\"x-agentcube-session-id\"] == \"test-session\"\n510: \n511:     def test_invoke_sets_content_type_header(self):\n512:         \"\"\"GIVEN invoke called\n513:            WHEN headers constructed\n514:            THEN Content-Type: application/json included\"\"\"\n515:         client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n516:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n517:             namespace=\"default\",\n518:             agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n519:         )\n520:         client.session_id = \"test-session\"\n521:         mock_response = Mock()\n522:         client.session.post = Mock(return_value=mock_response)\n523:         \n524:         client.invoke(session_id=\"test-session\", payload={\"test\": \"data\"})\n525:         \n526:         headers = client.session.post.call_args[1]['headers']\n527:         assert headers[\"Content-Type\"] == \"application/json\"\n528: \n529:     def test_invoke_timeout_default(self):\n530:         \"\"\"GIVEN invoke called without timeout\n531:            WHEN request sent\n532:            THEN timeout tuple with instance default used\"\"\"\n533:         client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n534:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n535:             namespace=\"default\",\n536:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n537:             timeout=120,\n538:             connect_timeout=5.0\n539:         )\n540:         client.session_id = \"test-session\"\n541:         mock_response = Mock()\n542:         client.session.post = Mock(return_value=mock_response)\n543:         \n544:         client.invoke(session_id=\"test-session\", payload={\"test\": \"data\"})\n545:         \n546:         timeout = client.session.post.call_args[1]['timeout']\n547:         assert timeout == (5.0, 120)\n548: \n549:     def test_invoke_timeout_override(self):\n550:         \"\"\"GIVEN invoke called with timeout=60\n551:            WHEN request sent\n552:            THEN timeout tuple uses override\"\"\"\n553:         client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n554:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n555:             namespace=\"default\",\n556:             agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n557:         )\n558:         client.session_id = \"test-session\"\n559:         mock_response = Mock()\n560:         client.session.post = Mock(return_value=mock_response)\n561:         \n562:         client.invoke(session_id=\"test-session\", payload={\"test\": \"data\"}, timeout=60)\n563:         \n564:         timeout = client.session.post.call_args[1]['timeout']\n565:         assert timeout == (client.connect_timeout, 60)\n566: \n567:     def test_invoke_returns_response(self):\n568:         \"\"\"GIVEN invoke completes successfully\n569:            WHEN response received\n570:            THEN requests.Response object returned\"\"\"\n571:         client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n572:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n573:             namespace=\"default\",\n574:             agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n575:         )\n576:         client.session_id = \"test-session\"\n577:         mock_response = Mock()\n578:         client.session.post = Mock(return_value=mock_response)\n579:         \n580:         result = client.invoke(session_id=\"test-session\", payload={\"test\": \"data\"})\n581:         \n582:         assert result is mock_response\n583: \n584: \n585: class TestAgentRuntimeDataPlaneClientClose:\n586:     def test_close_calls_session_close(self):\n587:         \"\"\"GIVEN close() called\n588:            WHEN method executes\n589:            THEN session.close() called\"\"\"\n590:         client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n591:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n592:             namespace=\"default\",\n593:             agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n594:         )\n595:         client.session.close = Mock()\n596:         client.close()\n597:         client.session.close.assert_called_once()\n598: ```\n599: \n600: ### Test Coverage Targets\n601: \n602: | Module | Target | Key Scenarios |\n603: |--------|--------|---------------|\n604: | `agent_runtime.py` | 90% | Bootstrap, invoke, context manager, error cases |\n605: | `agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | 95% | URL computation, bootstrap, invoke, session header |\n606: \n607: ### Integration Tests\n608: \n609: ```python\n610: @pytest.fixture\n611: def agent_runtime_client():\n612:     \"\"\"Integration test fixture for AgentRuntimeClient\"\"\"\n613:     client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n614:         agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n615:         router_url=os.getenv(\"TEST_ROUTER_URL\", \"http://localhost:8080\"),\n616:         namespace=\"test\"\n617:     )\n618:     yield client\n619:     client.close()\n620: \n621: def test_agent_invoke_integration(agent_runtime_client):\n622:     \"\"\"Test agent invocation against live Router\"\"\"\n623:     response = agent_runtime_client.invoke({\n624:         \"action\": \"test\",\n625:         \"payload\": {\"key\": \"value\"}\n626:     })\n627:     assert response is not None\n628: ```\n629: \n630: ## Module Exports\n631: \n632: ### `agentcube/__init__.py`\n633: \n634: ```python\n635: from .code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n636: from .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n637: \n638: __all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n639: ```\n640: \n641: ### `agentcube/clients/__init__.py`\n642: \n643: ```python\n644: from .control_plane import ControlPlaneClient\n645: from .code_interpreter_data_plane import CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n646: from .agent_runtime_data_plane import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n647: \n648: __all__ = [\n649:     \"ControlPlaneClient\",\n650:     \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n651:     \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\",\n652: ]\n653: ```\n654: \n655: ## Implementation Checklist\n656: \n657: - [ ] Create `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` with `AgentRuntimeClient` class\n658: - [ ] Create `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` with `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class\n659: - [ ] Update `agentcube/__init__.py` to export `AgentRuntimeClient`\n660: - [ ] Update `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` to export `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n661: - [ ] Implement router URL resolution (arg → `ROUTER_URL` env → error)\n662: - [ ] Implement session bootstrap via GET request\n663: - [ ] Implement payload invocation via POST with session header\n664: - [ ] Implement context manager protocol (`__enter__`, `__exit__`)\n665: - [ ] Implement timeout defaults (120s read / 5.0s connect)\n666: - [ ] Implement per-call timeout override\n667: - [ ] Use lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id` header consistently\n668: - [ ] Implement HTTP session with connection pooling (10/10)\n669: - [ ] Write unit tests for all scenarios\n670: - [ ] Verify code coverage >= 80%\n\n(End of file - total 670 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028: SDK AgentRuntimeClient — Technical Design\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `sdk-python`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n\nThis document provides technical implementation details for the `AgentRuntimeClient` feature in the AgentCube Python SDK.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Hierarchy\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│       AgentRuntimeClient                │\n│  (High-level Facade)                    │\n│  - agent_name                           │\n│  - namespace                            │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/design.md","time":{"start":1775877276408,"end":1775877276428}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877276433,"sessionID":"ses_28577793bffeWlqSBWZrdZ4b1w","part":{"id":"prt_d7a88be300010zyjsnlN5V2a14","messageID":"msg_d7a88a51f001qF4VBbO0JYZRp1","sessionID":"ses_28577793bffeWlqSBWZrdZ4b1w","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_2c1e224554a5417fa57b2326","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification — AR-028: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **Module:** `sdk-python`  \n6: **Language:** Python  \n7: **Size:** M  \n8: **Type:** Implementation of AgentRuntimeClient for invoking Agent Runtime workloads via Router\n9: \n10: **Base Specs:** python-sdk/design.md, python-sdk/spec.md\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements & Scenarios\n15: \n16: ### REQ-028.1: AgentRuntimeClient Initialization\n17: \n18: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement `AgentRuntimeClient` class with configuration resolution for router_url, session_id, and timeout parameters.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Initialize with explicit session_id\n21: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is provided to `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__`\n22: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n23: - **THEN** `self.session_id` SHALL be set to the provided value and bootstrap SHALL NOT be called\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Initialize without session_id triggers bootstrap\n26: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is `None`\n27: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n28: - **THEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` SHALL be called and result assigned to `self.session_id`\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Router URL from argument\n31: - **GIVEN** `router_url` is provided as argument\n32: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n33: - **THEN** `self.router_url` SHALL be set to the provided argument\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Router URL from environment variable\n36: - **GIVEN** `router_url` is `None` and `ROUTER_URL` environment variable is set\n37: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n38: - **THEN** `self.router_url` SHALL be set from `os.getenv(\"ROUTER_URL\")`\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Missing router_url raises ValueError\n41: - **GIVEN** `router_url` is `None` and `ROUTER_URL` environment variable is not set\n42: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n43: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` with message containing \"router_url must be provided\"\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Timeout defaults\n46: - **GIVEN** `timeout` and `connect_timeout` are not specified\n47: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n48: - **THEN** `self.timeout` SHALL default to `120` and `self.connect_timeout` SHALL default to `5.0`\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Namespace default\n51: - **GIVEN** `namespace` is not specified\n52: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n53: - **THEN** `self.namespace` SHALL default to `\"default\"`\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Verbose logging configuration\n56: - **GIVEN** `verbose=True` is specified\n57: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n58: - **THEN** logger level SHALL be set to `DEBUG`\n59: \n60: #### Scenario: Verbose default is False\n61: - **GIVEN** `verbose` is not specified\n62: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n63: - **THEN** logger level SHALL default to `INFO`\n64: \n65: ---\n66: \n67: ### REQ-028.2: AgentRuntimeClient Context Manager\n68: \n69: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement context manager protocol (`__enter__`, `__exit__`) for automatic resource cleanup.\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Context manager entry\n72: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used in `with` statement\n73: - **WHEN** entering the context\n74: - **THEN** `__enter__` SHALL return `self`\n75: \n76: #### Scenario: Context manager normal exit\n77: - **GIVEN** context block completes without exception\n78: - **WHEN** exiting the context\n79: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()`\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: Context manager exception exit\n82: - **GIVEN** context block raises an exception\n83: - **WHEN** exiting the context\n84: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()` and allow exception to propagate\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ### REQ-028.3: AgentRuntimeClient.invoke Method\n89: \n90: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement `invoke(payload, timeout=None)` method for sending JSON payloads to the agent runtime.\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Invoke with payload\n93: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is initialized\n94: - **WHEN** `invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"})` is called\n95: - **THEN** it SHALL call `dp_client.invoke()` with session_id and payload\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Invoke returns parsed JSON\n98: - **GIVEN** `dp_client.invoke()` returns a response object\n99: - **WHEN** `invoke()` completes\n100: - **THEN** it SHALL return `response.json()` (parsed JSON)\n101: \n102: #### Scenario: Invoke without session_id raises\n103: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is `None` or falsy\n104: - **WHEN** `invoke()` is called\n105: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Invoke with timeout override\n108: - **GIVEN** `invoke(payload, timeout=60)` is called\n109: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n110: - **THEN** timeout `60` SHALL be passed to `dp_client.invoke()`\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: Invoke without timeout uses default\n113: - **GIVEN** `invoke(payload)` is called without timeout\n114: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n115: - **THEN** `timeout=None` SHALL be passed to `dp_client.invoke()` (uses instance default)\n116: \n117: ---\n118: \n119: ### REQ-028.4: AgentRuntimeClient.close Method\n120: \n121: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement `close()` method for closing the underlying HTTP session.\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: Close calls dp_client.close\n124: - **GIVEN** `close()` is called\n125: - **WHEN** the method executes\n126: - **THEN** it SHALL call `self.dp_client.close()`\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Close logs debug message\n129: - **GIVEN** `close()` is called\n130: - **WHEN** the method completes\n131: - **THEN** it SHALL log debug message \"AgentRuntimeClient closed\"\n132: \n133: ---\n134: \n135: ### REQ-028.5: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Initialization\n136: \n137: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` with base URL computation from router_url, namespace, and agent_name.\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: Base URL computation\n140: - **GIVEN** `router_url=\"http://router:8080\"`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `agent_name=\"test-agent\"`\n141: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n142: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://router:8080/v1/namespaces/default/agent-runtimes/test-agent/invocations/`\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: Session constant\n145: - **GIVEN** class is defined\n146: - **WHEN** accessed\n147: - **THEN** `SESSION_HEADER` SHALL equal `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: HTTP session creation with pooling\n150: - **GIVEN** client initializes\n151: - **WHEN** `create_session()` is called\n152: - **THEN** it SHALL use `pool_connections=10` and `pool_maxsize=10` by default\n153: \n154: #### Scenario: Timeout defaults\n155: - **GIVEN** `timeout` and `connect_timeout` are not specified\n156: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n157: - **THEN** `self.timeout` SHALL default to `120` and `self.connect_timeout` SHALL default to `5.0`\n158: \n159: ---\n160: \n161: ### REQ-028.6: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.bootstrap_session_id\n162: \n163: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement `bootstrap_session_id()` method that GETs the invocation URL and extracts session ID from response header.\n164: \n165: #### Scenario: Successful session bootstrap\n166: - **GIVEN** Router responds with `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n167: - **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n168: - **THEN** it SHALL return the header value\n169: \n170: #### Scenario: Missing session header raises\n171: - **GIVEN** Router response lacks `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n172: - **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n173: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")`\n174: \n175: #### Scenario: Bootstrap sets session header\n176: - **GIVEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` succeeds\n177: - **WHEN** it completes\n178: - **THEN** `self.session.headers[\"x-agentcube-session-id\"]` SHALL be set to the bootstrapped value\n179: \n180: #### Scenario: Bootstrap makes GET request\n181: - **GIVEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n182: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n183: - **THEN** it SHALL be `GET self.base_url` with timeout `(connect_timeout, timeout)`\n184: \n185: ---\n186: \n187: ### REQ-028.7: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.invoke\n188: \n189: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement `invoke(session_id, payload, timeout=None)` method for POSTing JSON payloads to the agent runtime.\n190: \n191: #### Scenario: Invoke sends POST request\n192: - **GIVEN** `invoke()` is called with payload\n193: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n194: - **THEN** it SHALL be `POST self.base_url` with JSON body\n195: \n196: #### Scenario: Invoke sets session header\n197: - **GIVEN** `invoke()` is called\n198: - **WHEN** headers are set\n199: - **THEN** `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` SHALL be included\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: Invoke sets Content-Type header\n202: - **GIVEN** `invoke()` is called\n203: - **WHEN** headers are set\n204: - **THEN** `Content-Type: application/json` SHALL be included\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: Invoke timeout tuple default\n207: - **GIVEN** `invoke()` is called without timeout\n208: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n209: - **THEN** timeout SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` tuple\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: Invoke timeout override\n212: - **GIVEN** `invoke(..., timeout=60)` is called\n213: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n214: - **THEN** timeout SHALL be `(connect_timeout, 60)`\n215: \n216: #### Scenario: Invoke returns response object\n217: - **GIVEN** `invoke()` completes successfully\n218: - **WHEN** response is received\n219: - **THEN** it SHALL return the `requests.Response` object\n220: \n221: #### Scenario: Invoke raises on HTTP error\n222: - **GIVEN** Server returns HTTP error status\n223: - **WHEN** `invoke()` receives response\n224: - **THEN** `response.raise_for_status()` SHALL be called (raises `requests.HTTPError`)\n225: \n226: ---\n227: \n228: ### REQ-028.8: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.close\n229: \n230: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement `close()` method for closing the underlying HTTP session.\n231: \n232: #### Scenario: Close calls session.close\n233: - **GIVEN** `close()` is called\n234: - **WHEN** the method executes\n235: - **THEN** it SHALL call `self.session.close()`\n236: \n237: #### Scenario: Close logs debug message\n238: - **GIVEN** `close()` is called\n239: - **WHEN** the method completes\n240: - **THEN** logger SHALL log debug message \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient closed\"\n241: \n242: ---\n243: \n244: ### REQ-028.9: Module Exports\n245: \n246: **Requirement:** The system SHALL export `AgentRuntimeClient` and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` in appropriate `__init__.py` files.\n247: \n248: #### Scenario: Root package exports AgentRuntimeClient\n249: - **GIVEN** `agentcube/__init__.py` is imported\n250: - **WHEN** `__all__` is inspected\n251: - **THEN** it SHALL contain `\"AgentRuntimeClient\"`\n252: \n253: #### Scenario: Import AgentRuntimeClient from root\n254: - **GIVEN** `agentcube` package is installed\n255: - **WHEN** `from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient` is executed\n256: - **THEN** import SHALL succeed\n257: \n258: #### Scenario: Clients subpackage exports AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n259: - **GIVEN** `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` is imported\n260: - **WHEN** `__all__` is inspected\n261: - **THEN** it SHALL contain `\"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"`\n262: \n263: #### Scenario: Import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient from clients\n264: - **GIVEN** `agentcube` package is installed\n265: - **WHEN** `from agentcube.clients import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is executed\n266: - **THEN** import SHALL succeed\n267: \n268: ---\n269: \n270: ### REQ-028.10: Session Header Naming\n271: \n272: **Requirement:** The system SHALL use lowercase header name `x-agentcube-session-id` for all SDK Router requests.\n273: \n274: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient SESSION_HEADER constant\n275: - **GIVEN** class constant `SESSION_HEADER` is defined\n276: - **WHEN** accessed\n277: - **THEN** it SHALL equal `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"` (lowercase)\n278: \n279: #### Scenario: Bootstrap header extraction\n280: - **GIVEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` reads response header\n281: - **WHEN** extracting header value\n282: - **THEN** it SHALL use lowercase key `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n283: \n284: #### Scenario: Invoke request header\n285: - **GIVEN** `invoke()` sets request headers\n286: - **WHEN** header dict is constructed\n287: - **THEN** it SHALL use `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"` as key (lowercase)\n288: \n289: ---\n290: \n291: ## Data Types\n292: \n293: ```python\n294: # AgentRuntimeClient constructor signature\n295: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n296:     def __init__(\n297:         self,\n298:         agent_name: str,\n299:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n300:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n301:         verbose: bool = False,\n302:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n303:         timeout: int = 120,\n304:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n305:     ) -> None: ...\n306: \n307: # AgentRuntimeClient public methods\n308: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n309:     def __enter__(self) -> \"AgentRuntimeClient\": ...\n310:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n311:     def invoke(self, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any: ...\n312:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n313: \n314: # AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient constructor signature\n315: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n316:     SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n317:     \n318:     def __init__(\n319:         self,\n320:         router_url: str,\n321:         namespace: str,\n322:         agent_name: str,\n323:         timeout: int = 120,\n324:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n325:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n326:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n327:     ) -> None: ...\n328: \n329: # AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient public methods\n330: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n331:     def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str: ...\n332:     def invoke(\n333:         self,\n334:         session_id: str,\n335:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n336:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n337:     ) -> requests.Response: ...\n338:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n339: ```\n340: \n341: ---\n342: \n343: ## HTTP Contracts\n344: \n345: ### Agent Runtime Data Plane\n346: \n347: | Operation | Method | URL | Headers | Body |\n348: |-----------|--------|-----|---------|------|\n349: | Bootstrap session | GET | `{router}/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agent-runtimes/{agent}/invocations/` | (none) | (none) |\n350: | Invoke agent | POST | `{base_url}` | `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `{\"key\": \"value\", ...}` |\n351: \n352: ### Response Headers\n353: \n354: | Header | Purpose | Required |\n355: |--------|---------|----------|\n356: | `x-agentcube-session-id` | Session identifier from bootstrap | Yes (on GET) |\n357: \n358: ---\n359: \n360: ## Error Handling\n361: \n362: | Error | Condition | Exception Type |\n363: |-------|-----------|----------------|\n364: | Missing router_url | Neither argument nor `ROUTER_URL` env var provided | `ValueError` |\n365: | Missing session header | Bootstrap response lacks `x-agentcube-session-id` | `ValueError` |\n366: | Invoke without session | `invoke()` called with falsy `session_id` | `ValueError` |\n367: | HTTP error | Server returns 4xx/5xx status | `requests.HTTPError` |\n368: | Network error | Connection refused, timeout, etc. | `requests.RequestException` |\n369: \n370: ---\n371: \n372: ## Environment Variables\n373: \n374: | Variable | Description | Default |\n375: |----------|-------------|---------|\n376: | `ROUTER_URL` | Router base URL for Agent Runtime | (required) |\n377: | `LOG_LEVEL` | Logging level (if used by get_logger) | INFO |\n378: \n379: ---\n380: \n381: ## Dependencies\n382: \n383: From `pyproject.toml`:\n384: \n385: ```toml\n386: dependencies = [\n387:     \"requests\",              # HTTP client\n388:     \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",         # JWT token handling\n389:     \"cryptography\",          # Cryptographic operations\n390: ]\n391: \n392: requires-python = \">=3.10\"\n393: ```\n394: \n395: ---\n396: \n397: ## Acceptance Checklist\n398: \n399: - [ ] `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` — `AgentRuntimeClient` class implemented\n400: - [ ] `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` — `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class implemented\n401: - [ ] `agentcube/__init__.py` — exports `AgentRuntimeClient` in `__all__`\n402: - [ ] `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` — exports `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` in `__all__`\n403: - [ ] Router URL resolution from argument or `ROUTER_URL` env var\n404: - [ ] Session bootstrapping via GET on invocation endpoint\n405: - [ ] Payload invocation via POST with session header\n406: - [ ] Context manager protocol (`__enter__`, `__exit__`)\n407: - [ ] `invoke()` raises `ValueError` without initialized session\n408: - [ ] Bootstrap raises `ValueError` if header missing\n409: - [ ] Timeout defaults: 120s read / 5.0s connect\n410: - [ ] Per-call timeout override support\n411: - [ ] HTTP session with connection pooling (10/10)\n412: - [ ] Lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id` header usage\n413: - [ ] Unit tests for session bootstrapping\n414: - [ ] Unit tests for invoke with/without timeout\n415: - [ ] Unit tests for context manager cleanup\n416: - [ ] Unit tests for error cases\n417: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80% for AgentRuntimeClient\n418: \n419: ---\n420: \n421: ## Open Questions\n422: \n423: 1. Should `invoke()` expose additional response metadata beyond parsed JSON (e.g., status code, headers)?\n424: 2. Should retry logic be added for transient HTTP failures?\n425: 3. Should streaming response support be added for long-running agent operations?\n426: 4. Should agent runtime discovery (list available agents) be supported?\n\n(End of file - total 426 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification — AR-028: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `sdk-python`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Type:** Implementation of AgentRuntimeClient for invoking Agent Runtime workloads via Router\n\n**Base Specs:** python-sdk/design.md, python-sdk/spec.md\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-028.1: AgentRuntimeClient Initialization\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL implement `AgentRuntimeClient` class with configuration resolution for router_url, session_id, and timeout parameters.\n\n#### Scenario: Initialize with explicit session_id","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775877276410,"end":1775877276431}}}}
