mespace`, `agent_name`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n36:   - Compute `base_url` from `router_url` + `/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n37:   - Create session with `create_session()`\n38:   - Initialize logger\n39:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n40:   - Verify: Base URL computed correctly, session initialized\n41: \n42: - [ ] **T2.3** Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.bootstrap_session_id()`\n43:   - GET request to `self.base_url`\n44:   - Timeout: `(connect_timeout, timeout)`\n45:   - Extract `x-agentcube-session-id` from response headers\n46:   - Raise `ValueError` if header missing\n47:   - Return session ID string\n48:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n49:   - Verify: Session ID extracted or ValueError raised\n50: \n51: - [ ] **T2.4** Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.invoke()`\n52:   - Parameters: `session_id`, `payload: Dict[str, Any]`, `timeout: Optional[float]`\n53:   - Set headers: `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json`\n54:   - POST JSON payload to `self.base_url`\n55:   - Apply timeout: use override or instance default\n56:   - Return `requests.Response`\n57:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n58:   - Verify: Request sent with correct headers and timeout\n59: \n60: - [ ] **T2.5** Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.close()`\n61:   - Call `self.session.close()`\n62:   - Log cleanup action\n63:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n64:   - Verify: HTTP session closed\n65: \n66: ---\n67: \n68: ## Phase 3: High-Level Client\n69: \n70: - [ ] **T3.1** Create `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n71:   - Import `AgentRuntimeClient`, dependencies (`AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`, `os`, `logging`)\n72:   - Define class\n73:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n74:   - Verify: Module structure correct\n75: \n76: - [ ] **T3.2** Implement `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__()`\n77:   - Parameters: `agent_name`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `router_url=None`, `verbose=False`, `session_id=None`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`\n78:   - Store instance attributes\n79:   - Initialize logger with verbose level\n80:   - Resolve `router_url` from arg or `ROUTER_URL` env var\n81:   - Raise `ValueError` if router_url missing\n82:   - Bootstrap session_id if not provided via `_bootstrap_session_id()`\n83:   - Create `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n84:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n85:   - Verify: Client instantiates, session bootstrapped or reused\n86: \n87: - [ ] **T3.3** Implement `AgentRuntimeClient._bootstrap_session_id()`\n88:   - Create temporary `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n89:   - Call `bootstrap_session_id()`\n90:   - Store result as `self.session_id`\n91:   - Close temporary client\n92:   - Return session ID\n93:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n94:   - Verify: Session ID bootstrapped from endpoint\n95: \n96: - [ ] **T3.4** Implement `AgentRuntimeClient.__enter__()` and `__exit__()`\n97:   - `__enter__`: return `self`\n98:   - `__exit__`: call `self.close()`\n99:   - Support context manager protocol\n100:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n101:   - Verify: `with` statement works\n102: \n103: - [ ] **T3.5** Implement `AgentRuntimeClient.invoke()`\n104:   - Parameters: `payload: Dict[str, Any]`, `timeout: Optional[float] = None`\n105:   - Check `session_id` is set, raise `ValueError` if not\n106:   - Call `dp_client.invoke()` with session_id, payload, timeout\n107:   - Return `response.json()`\n108:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n109:   - Verify: Invocation returns parsed JSON\n110: \n111: - [ ] **T3.6** Implement `AgentRuntimeClient.close()`\n112:   - Call `dp_client.close()`\n113:   - Log cleanup action\n114:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n115:   - Verify: Resources cleaned up\n11