{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877314788,"sessionID":"ses_28577793bffeWlqSBWZrdZ4b1w","part":{"id":"prt_d7a895351001NS9y0895cB2r7R","messageID":"msg_d7a8940e1001nWf5xzAPNfRsI3","sessionID":"ses_28577793bffeWlqSBWZrdZ4b1w","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_ba2fcb7f8eae43f69b7df688","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/README.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube Python SDK\n2: \n3: Python SDK for invoking Agent Runtime workloads in the AgentCube platform.\n4: \n5: ## Installation\n6: \n7: Install from source:\n8: \n9: ```bash\n10: cd sdk-python\n11: pip install .\n12: ```\n13: \n14: Install with development dependencies:\n15: \n16: ```bash\n17: pip install -e \".[dev]\"\n18: ```\n19: \n20: ## Requirements\n21: \n22: - Python 3.10+\n23: - requests >= 2.28.0\n24: - urllib3 >= 1.26.0\n25: \n26: ## Quick Start\n27: \n28: ### Basic Usage\n29: \n30: The recommended way to use `AgentRuntimeClient` is with the context manager pattern:\n31: \n32: ```python\n33: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n34: \n35: with AgentRuntimeClient(\n36:     agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n37:     namespace=\"default\",\n38:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n39: ) as client:\n40:     response = client.invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"})\n41:     print(response)\n42: ```\n43: \n44: ### Environment Variable Configuration\n45: \n46: You can set the `ROUTER_URL` environment variable instead of providing it explicitly:\n47: \n48: ```bash\n49: export ROUTER_URL=\"http://router:8080\"\n50: ```\n51: \n52: ```python\n53: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n54: \n55: # router_url will be read from ROUTER_URL environment variable\n56: with AgentRuntimeClient(\n57:     agent_name=\"my-agent\"\n58: ) as client:\n59:     response = client.invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"})\n60:     print(response)\n61: ```\n62: \n63: ### Explicit Session ID\n64: \n65: To reuse an existing session instead of bootstrapping a new one:\n66: \n67: ```python\n68: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n69: \n70: # Bootstrap a session first\n71: with AgentRuntimeClient(\n72:     agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n73:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n74: ) as client1:\n75:     session_id = client1.session_id\n76: \n77: # Reuse the session in another client\n78: with AgentRuntimeClient(\n79:     agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n80:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n81:     session_id=session_id  # Skip bootstrap\n82: ) as client2:\n83:     response = client2.invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"})\n84:     print(response)\n85: ```\n86: \n87: ## API Reference\n88: \n89: ### AgentRuntimeClient\n90: \n91: High-level client for invoking Agent Runtime workloads.\n92: \n93: #### Constructor\n94: \n95: ```python\n96: AgentRuntimeClient(\n97:     agent_name: str,\n98:     namespace: str = \"default\",\n99:     router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n100:     verbose: bool = False,\n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 329. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube Python SDK\n\nPython SDK for invoking Agent Runtime workloads in the AgentCube platform.\n\n## Installation\n\nInstall from source:\n\n```bash\ncd sdk-python\npip install .\n```\n\nInstall with development dependencies:\n\n```bash\npip install -e \".[dev]\"\n```\n\n## Requirements","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/README.md","time":{"start":1775877314771,"end":1775877314787}}}}
